      "questionParts": [
        "Solve the first-order linear ODE:",
        " y' + 2y = 4 "
      ],
      "options": [
        " y = 2 + Ce^{-2x} ",
        " y = 4x + C ",
        " y = Ce^{2x} ",
        " y = 2e^{-2x} + C "
      ],
      "correctAnswer": " y = 2 + Ce^{-2x} ",
      "explanationParts": [
        "**Step 1:** Identify as linear ODE:  y' + P(x)y = Q(x)  with  P(x) = 2 ,  Q(x) = 4 .",
        "**Step 2:** Compute integrating factor:",
        " \\mu(x) = e^{\\int 2 \\, dx} = e^{2x} ",
        "**Step 3:** Multiply through and integrate:",
        " e^{2x}y' + 2e^{2x}y = 4e^{2x} \\implies \\frac{d}{dx}(e^{2x}y) = 4e^{2x} ",
        " e^{2x}y = 2e^{2x} + C \\implies y = 2 + Ce^{-2x} "
      ]
    },
